\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}

The iter-029 lemmas materialise Step 1 (the abstract LES) and Step 2 (the corner-identification simp lemmas) of the iter-028 Serre-finiteness sketch (Section~\ref{sec:scheme_affineCoverMVSquare}); iter-030 materialised Step 2.5 (the toModuleKSheaf specialisation, a routine binding so downstream code paths can reference the LES on the structure sheaf of a curve directly); iter-031 materialised the \emph{source-object} half of Step 3 (the cover-totality identification at the sheaf level); iter-032 materialised the \emph{Ext-transport} half of Step 3 at universe $u+1$ (landing on $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$); iter-033 materialised the parallel \emph{Ext-transport} at universe $u$ (landing on $\Ext_u\,X_2\,F\,n$); iter-034 closed Step 3 by appending the Mathlib gap-fill $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUnivLinearEquiv}$ (universe-bump $\LinearEquiv$ upgrade of Mathlib's bare $\Equiv$ $\Ext.\mathtt{chgUniv}$) and composing iter-033 with it to produce the full bridge $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,T \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ for terminal $T$; iter-035 closed Step 3.5 (the \emph{corner-bridge}) by specialising the iter-034 universal bridge to the $X_4$ corner of an $\AffineCoverMVSquare$ — both an abstract sheaf form (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}) and a curve specialisation (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv_curve}); iter-036 (this iteration) appends the immediate \emph{finrank corollary} (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_finrank_HModule_eq_HModule_prime_X4_curve}) — landing the genus carrier $\mathrm{finrank}_k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$ on the explicit corner $X_4$ via $\LinearEquiv.\mathtt{finrank\_eq}$. The remaining work — Step 4 (affine vanishing $H^{>0}(\Spec A, \mathcal F) = 0$, possibly multi-iteration depending on Mathlib state) and Step 5 (finiteness of each $H^0$ piece, hence of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$) — is iter-037+.

