\subsection{Module.Finite transport via the corner-bridge (iter-037)}

The iter-035 corner-bridge $\AffineCoverMVSquare.\HModulePrime\_X_4\_\mathtt{linearEquiv}$ is a $k$-linear isomorphism, so the property \emph{``the underlying $k$-module is finite''} transports across it: if $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,X_4$ is finite over $k$, so is $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$. This is the algebraic counterpart of the iter-036 finrank corollary — the same one-step transport, but now landing on $\Module.\mathtt{Finite}$ rather than $\mathrm{finrank}$. It is the precise downstream hypothesis $\mathtt{smoothOfRelativeDimension\_genus}$ (Jacobian.lean) will eventually consume. Step 4 (the actual proof that $\HModulePrime\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n\,X_4$ is finite — typically via affine-vanishing and the finiteness of $H^0(\Spec A, \mathcal O_{\Spec A}) = A$ for $A$ a finitely generated $k$-algebra) is iter-038+.

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[$\HModule$-finiteness via $X_4$ corner, abstract sheaf form, iter-037]
  \label{thm:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_module_finite_HModule_of_HModule_prime_X4}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.AffineCoverMVSquare.module_finite_HModule_of_HModule'_X₄}
  \uses{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv, def:Scheme_HModule, def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
  Let $k$ be a field, $X : \Scheme$, $S : X.\AffineCoverMVSquare$, $F : \Sheaf\,(\mathtt{Opens.grothendieckTopology}\,X.\mathtt{toTopCat})\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$, $n \in \mathbb{N}$, and assume $\HasExt_u$ and $\HasExt_{u+1}$ for the same sheaf category. If $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(S.\mathtt{toMayerVietorisSquare}.\mathtt{toSquare}.X_4)$ is a finite $k$-module, then so is $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}\leanok
  Apply Mathlib's $\Module.\mathtt{Finite.equiv}$ ($\mathtt{Mathlib/RingTheory/Finiteness/Basic.lean}$, signature $(e : M \equiv_R N) [\Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,R\,M] : \Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,R\,N$) to the iter-035 corner-bridge $\AffineCoverMVSquare.\HModulePrime\_X_4\_\mathtt{linearEquiv}$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_AffineCoverMVSquare_HModule_prime_X4_linearEquiv}), which carries $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,X_4 \equiv_{\Module k} \HModule\,k\,F\,n$ in exactly the orientation $\Module.\mathtt{Finite.equiv}$ wants (LHS hypothesis, RHS conclusion). Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-037 pass) confirms the one-liner $\Module.\mathtt{Finite.equiv}\,(S.\HModulePrime\_X_4\_\mathtt{linearEquiv}\,k\,F\,n)$ typechecks end-to-end with kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{theorem}\leanok
